{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe diff-scope filter keeps a detector match only when `location.file` is EXACTLY equal to an\nentry in `changed_files` (`src/rebar/llm/code_review/detectors.py:74`, `if loc and loc in\nchanged:`), with neither side normalized. A location and a changed-file entry that denote the\nSAME file with different spellings (`./app.py`, an absolute path under repo_root, `a//b.py`\nrepeated separators, a unicode NFC/NFD variant) compare unequal, so a real high-severity\nsecurity match is silently dropped. VALIDATED.\n\n## Decision: normalize BOTH sides at this boundary\nAdd a small canonicalizer applied to `location.file` AND each `changed_files` entry before the\nmembership test ŌĆö a pure textual canonical form (no filesystem access, since diff-scope paths\nneed not exist on disk):\n1. If the path is absolute AND under `repo_root`, make it relative to `repo_root` (both sides\n   then live in the same relative space; the upstream contract already intends repo-relative).\n2. `os.path.normpath` ŌĆö collapses `./`, repeated separators (`a//b` ŌåÆ `a/b`), and `..`.\n3. `unicodedata.normalize(\"NFC\", ŌĆ”)` ŌĆö so a composed/decomposed unicode filename matches.\nSymlink resolution (realpath) is explicitly OUT OF SCOPE: it requires the file to exist on\ndisk, which a diff-scope path need not; this ticket canonicalizes spelling, not inode identity\n(noted in a code comment).\n\n## What\n1. `detectors.py`: add `_canonical_path(p, repo_root)` (relativize-under-repo_root ŌåÆ normpath ŌåÆ\n   NFC) and apply it to both `loc` and every `changed_files` entry (build the `changed` set from\n   canonicalized entries; canonicalize `loc` before the `in` test).\n2. `tests/unit/test_code_review_ws5.py`: variant-path matching tests (RED-first ŌĆö they fail\n   against the current exact-match code, pass after canonicalization).\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/detectors.py` ŌĆö canonicalize both sides of the diff-scope filter.\n- `tests/unit/test_code_review_ws5.py` ŌĆö variant-path-form tests.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `location.file` and `changed_files` are both canonicalized (relativize-under-repo_root +\n      normpath + NFC) before the membership test.\n- [ ] Tests: a match whose `location.file` is `./app.py`, an absolute path under repo_root,\n      `a//b.py` (repeated separators), and an NFC/NFD unicode variant each STILL matches its\n      changed-file entry `app.py` / `a/b.py` / the unicode name ŌĆö the high-severity match is\n      retained.\n- [ ] A genuinely-different file (e.g. `other.py` not in `changed_files`) still does NOT match.\n- [ ] `make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783804912373950001,"uuid":"f75b620d-3272-4a7c-8b1e-dfa5bcb3f2b0"}